          "text": "Implement the following plan:\n\n# Self-Update System for Desent (Docker-Only)\n\n## Context\n\nDesent is a self-hosted streaming platform. Streamers deploy via Docker Compose (Go server + Next.js frontend). Currently, updating requires SSH and manual `docker compose pull && up`. Streamers need a one-click update from the admin web UI.\n\n**Release pipeline:** GitHub Releases (tags like `v1.2.3`) + Docker Hub images tagged with the same version.\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\n```\nAdmin clicks \"Update\" in UI\n    │\n    ▼\nGo server checks GitHub Releases API for latest tag\n    │\n    ▼\nGo server pulls new Docker images via Docker Engine API (Unix socket)\n    │\n    ▼\nGo server recreates web container (safe — server is still running)\n    │\n    ▼\nGo server launches a helper container (from current image, --update-self flag)\n    │\n    ▼\nHelper container recreates server container (stop old → create new → start new)\n    │\n    ▼\nNew server container starts with new version\n    │\n    ▼\nAdmin UI polls /api/version → detects new version → shows \"updated!\"\n```\n\n**Key insight:** The server can't recreate its own container (it gets killed when stopped). So it spawns a short-lived helper container that does the server-self-replacement. The helper uses the **current** server image (always available locally) with a special `update-self` CLI flag.\n\n**Zero additional dependencies:** Uses Docker Engine API via HTTP to Unix socket (`net/http` stdlib). No `docker` CLI needed in the image.\n\n## Files to Create\n\n### `internal/update/docker.go` — Docker Engine API client\n\nMinimal HTTP client that talks to Docker daemon via `/var/run/docker.sock`:\n\n```go\ntype dockerClient struct{ httpClient *http.Client }\n\nfunc newDockerClient() *dockerClient  // Uses net.Dial(\"unix\", socketPath) transport\n\n// Image operations\nfunc (c *dockerClient) PullImage(ctx, image, tag string, onProgress func(status string, current, total int64)) error\n// POST /images/create?fromImage=...&tag=... — streams JSON progress events\n\n// Container operations\nfunc (c *dockerClient) ListContainers(ctx, labels map[string]string) ([]ContainerSummary, error)\n// GET /containers/json?filters={\"label\":[\"com.docker.compose.service=web\"]}\n\nfunc (c *dockerClient) InspectContainer(ctx, id string) (*ContainerInspect, error)\n// GET /containers/{id}/json\n\nfunc (c *dockerClient) StopContainer(ctx, id string, timeoutSec int) error\n// POST /containers/{id}/stop?t=30\n\nfunc (c *dockerClient) RemoveContainer(ctx, id string) error\n// DELETE /containers/{id}\n\nfunc (c *dockerClient) CreateContainer(ctx, name string, body ContainerCreateBody) (string, error)\n// POST /containers/create?name=... — returns new container ID\n\nfunc (c *dockerClient) StartContainer(ctx, id string) error\n// POST /containers/{id}/start\n```\n\nResponse types (only the fields we need from Docker API):\n- `ContainerSummary` — Id, Names, Image, Labels, State\n- `ContainerInspect` — full container config (Config, HostConfig, NetworkSettings, Name)\n- `ContainerCreateBody` — mirrors Docker's create API (Image, Env, ExposedPorts, HostConfig with Binds/PortBindings/RestartPolicy, NetworkingConfig)\n\nDocker socket availability check: `SocketAvailable() bool` — stats `/var/run/docker.sock`.\n\n### `internal/update/updater.go` — Core update logic\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    CurrentVersion string // from ldflags\n    GitHubRepo     string // \"Desent-tech/desent\"\n    DataDir        string // for staging\n    ServerImage    string // Docker Hub: \"desent/server\"\n    WebImage       string // Docker Hub: \"desent/web\"\n    ComposeProject string // compose project name for label filtering\n}\n\ntype Updater struct {\n    cfg         Config\n    docker      *dockerClient\n    mu          sync.Mutex\n    updating    bool\n    progress    Progress\n    subscribers map[chan Progress]struct{}\n    cachedCheck *UpdateCheckResult\n    cacheExpiry time.Time\n}\n\ntype ProgressPhase string // idle|checking|downloading|applying|restarting|failed|complete\n\ntype Progress struct {\n    Phase           ProgressPhase `json:\"phase\"`\n    Percent         int           `json:\"percent\"`\n    BytesDownloaded int64         `json:\"bytes_downloaded\"`\n    BytesTotal      int64         `json:\"bytes_total\"`\n    Message         string        `json:\"message\"`\n    Error           string        `json:\"error,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype ReleaseInfo struct {\n    Version     string    `json:\"version\"`\n    PublishedAt time.Time `json:\"published_at\"`\n    ReleaseURL  string    `json:\"release_url\"`\n    Body        string    `json:\"body\"` // markdown changelog\n}\n\ntype UpdateCheckResult struct {\n    CurrentVersion  string       `json:\"current_version\"`\n    LatestVersion   string       `json:\"latest_version\"`\n    UpdateAvailable bool         `json:\"update_available\"`\n    Release         *ReleaseInfo `json:\"release,omitempty\"`\n    SocketAvailable bool         `json:\"socket_available\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Key methods:**\n\n`CheckForUpdate(ctx)` — Calls `GET https://api.github.com/repos/{owner}/{repo}/releases/latest`, compares semver tags, caches result for 5 minutes.\n\n`Apply(ctx)` — The main update flow (runs in background goroutine):\n1. **Phase: downloading** — Pull `ServerImage:newTag` and `WebImage:newTag` via Docker API with progress tracking\n2. **Phase: applying** — Recreate web container:\n   - Find web container by compose labels (`com.docker.compose.service=web`, `com.docker.compose.project=...`)\n   - Inspect → get full config\n   - Stop → Remove → Create (same config, new image) → Start\n3. **Phase: restarting** — Launch helper container:\n   - Get own container ID via `os.Hostname()`\n   - Inspect self → get current image name\n   - Create helper container from current image: `[\"/server\", \"update-self\", \"--container\", selfID, \"--image\", newServerImage+\":\"+newTag, \"--name\", selfName]`\n   - Mount Docker socket into helper, set `AutoRemove: true`\n   - Start helper container\n   - Send \"restarting\" progress to admin\n   - The main server keeps running until the helper stops it\n\n`RecreateContainer(docker, containerID, newImage)` — Reusable function used for both web (by main server) and server (by helper):\n1. Inspect container → save config\n2. Stop container (30s graceful timeout)\n3. Remove container\n4. Create new container with: same name, same env vars, same ports, same volumes, same networks, same restart policy — but new image\n5. Start new container\n6. If any step fails after stop, attempt rollback (recreate from old image)\n\n### `internal/update/handler.go` — HTTP endpoints\n\n```go\ntype Handler struct {\n    updater      *Updater\n    tokenService TokenValidator // interface for JWT validation\n}\n\nfunc (h *Handler) RegisterRoutes(mux *http.ServeMux, mw func(http.Handler) http.Handler) {\n    mux.Handle(\"GET /api/admin/update/check\", mw(http.HandlerFunc(h.checkUpdate)))\n    mux.Handle(\"POST /api/admin/update/apply\", mw(http.HandlerFunc(h.applyUpdate)))\n    // SSE uses query-param auth (EventSource can't set headers)\n    mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/admin/update/progress\", h.streamProgress)\n}\n```\n\n- `checkUpdate` — Returns `UpdateCheckResult` JSON\n- `applyUpdate` — If socket unavailable: 503 with error. If already updating: 409. Otherwise: starts background goroutine, returns 202\n- `streamProgress` — SSE with `?token=JWT` auth (validated manually, same pattern as WebSocket chat). Streams `Progress` JSON events. Sends current state immediately on connect.\n\n### `cmd/server/main.go` — update-self mode + wiring\n\nAdd early check before normal startup:\n```go\nfunc main() {\n    if len(os.Args) > 1 && os.Args[1] == \"update-self\" {\n        // Parse flags: --container, --image, --name\n        // Run RecreateContainer() using Docker API\n        // Exit 0 on success, 1 on failure\n        return\n    }\n    // ... existing startup code ...\n}\n```\n\nWire update handler after admin handler:\n```go\nupdater := update.NewUpdater(update.Config{\n    CurrentVersion: version,\n    GitHubRepo:     cfg.GitHubRepo,\n    ServerImage:    cfg.DockerServerImage,\n    WebImage:       cfg.DockerWebImage,\n    ComposeProject: cfg.ComposeProject,\n    DataDir:        cfg.DataDir,\n})\nupdateHandler := update.NewHandler(updater, tokenService)\nupdateHandler.RegisterRoutes(mux, adminMW)\n```\n\n## Files to Modify\n\n### `internal/config/config.go`\n\nAdd fields:\n```go\nGitHubRepo        string // GITHUB_REPO, default \"Desent-tech/desent\"\nDockerServerImage string // DOCKER_SERVER_IMAGE, default \"desent/server\"\nDockerWebImage    string // DOCKER_WEB_IMAGE, default \"desent/web\"\nComposeProject    string // COMPOSE_PROJECT, default \"desent\"\n```\n\n### `Dockerfile`\n\nNo changes needed — we don't need docker CLI since we use the Docker Engine API directly via HTTP.\n\n### `docker-compose.yml`\n\nAdd Docker socket mount to server service:\n```yaml\nserver:\n  image: ${DOCKER_SERVER_IMAGE:-desent/server}:${DESENT_VERSION:-latest}\n  volumes:\n    - /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock\n    - db-data:/data\n    - ./data:/app/data\n  # ... rest unchanged\n\nweb:\n  image: ${DOCKER_WEB_IMAGE:-desent/web}:${DESENT_VERSION:-latest}\n  # ... rest unchanged\n```\n\nProduction deployments use `image:` instead of `build:`. The socket mount is required for the update feature.\n\n### Frontend: `web/desent-web/apps/web/lib/api-types.ts`\n\nAdd:\n```typescript\nexport type UpdateCheckResult = {\n  current_version: string\n  latest_version: string\n  update_available: boolean\n  release?: {\n    version: string\n    published_at: string\n    release_url: string\n    body: string\n  }\n  socket_available: boolean\n}\n\nexport type UpdateProgress = {\n  phase: \"idle\" | \"checking\" | \"downloading\" | \"applying\" | \"restarting\" | \"failed\" | \"complete\"\n  percent: number\n  bytes_downloaded: number\n  bytes_total: number\n  message: string\n  error?: string\n}\n```\n\n### Frontend: `web/desent-web/apps/web/lib/api-client.ts`\n\nAdd methods:\n```typescript\ncheckForUpdate(): Promise<UpdateCheckResult>\napplyUpdate(): Promise<void>   // handles 202/409/503\nsubscribeUpdateProgress(onProgress): EventSource  // SSE with ?token= auth\n```\n\n### Frontend: `web/desent-web/apps/web/app/admin/layout.tsx`\n\nAdd nav item: `{ href: \"/admin/update\", label: \"update\", icon: ArrowsClockwise }`\n\n### Frontend: New file `web/desent-web/apps/web/app/admin/update/page.tsx`\n\nStates:\n1. **Loading** — checking on mount\n2. **Up to date** — current version, \"check again\" button\n3. **Update available** — version, changelog, \"update now\" with confirmation dialog\n4. **No socket** — Docker socket not mounted, shows instructions to mount it\n5. **Updating** — progress bar with phase labels, download progress\n6. **Restarting** — \"server is restarting...\" with polling loop on `/api/version` every 2s\n7. **Error** — error message with retry button\n\nAuto-reconnect after restart: poll `GET /api/version` up to 30 times (60s), compare response version with expected new version, reload page on match.\n\nUses same card styling as other admin pages (`bg-secondary rounded-2xl p-5`).\n\n## Safety\n\n- **Docker socket check**: If `/var/run/docker.sock` not available, update check still works but apply returns 503 with clear error\n- **Container recreation rollback**: If creating new container fails after removing old one, attempt to recreate from old image\n- **Concurrency guard**: Mutex prevents parallel updates\n- **Checksum**: Version comparison uses semver (no arbitrary code execution)\n- **Graceful stop**: 30s timeout for container stop (matches existing SIGTERM handling)\n- **Helper auto-cleanup**: Helper container uses AutoRemove — Docker removes it after exit\n- **GitHub rate limit**: 60 req/hour unauthenticated, 5-min cache prevents excessive calls\n\n## Implementation Order\n\n1. `internal/update/docker.go` — Docker Engine API client\n2. `internal/update/updater.go` — Check + Apply + RecreateContainer logic\n3. `internal/update/handler.go` — HTTP endpoints + SSE\n4. `internal/config/config.go` — add 4 config fields\n5. `cmd/server/main.go` — update-self mode + wiring\n6. `docker-compose.yml` — add socket mount, switch to `image:` for production\n7. `api-types.ts` — TypeScript types\n8. `api-client.ts` — API methods\n9. `app/admin/layout.tsx` — nav item\n10. `app/admin/update/page.tsx` — update page UI\n\n## Verification\n\n1. Build with `-X main.version=0.0.1` to simulate old version\n2. Set `GITHUB_REPO=Desent-tech/desent` (or any public repo with releases)\n3. Verify `GET /api/admin/update/check` returns update info\n4. Verify SSE: `curl -N \"localhost:8080/api/admin/update/progress?token=JWT\"`\n5. Test without socket: verify 503 response with clear error\n6. Test full update flow with Docker Compose (requires published images on Docker Hub)\n7. Test error cases: no releases, rate limited, network error, container recreation failure\n\n\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/m.ovchinnikov/.claude/projects/-Users-m-ovchinnikov-GolandProjects-desent/3e692d64-f3b4-496e-a337-aef8b25ea0f0.jsonl",
